                <note rend="inline" type="source">026 China/7–2149</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> of a Conversation With President <persName type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-21">July 21,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">China White Paper</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I informed the President of the reasons for the postponement of the date of
                    publication for one week, and of the possible objections by the NME. The
                    President was of the opinion that we should proceed with the publication as now
                    planned.</p>
                <p>I told him also of my discussion with Senator Connally and he approved the
                    arrangements for cooperation with the Committee which we were now making.</p>
            </div>
